      &lt;button class=&quot;color&quot; style=&quot;background-color: blue; color: white;&quot; type=&quot;button&quot; onclick=&quot;inline(event)&quot; data-value=&quot;blue&quot;&gt;Blue&lt;/button&gt;
    &lt;/div&gt;

&lt;!-- end snippet --&gt;

Alternatively, if you don&#39;t want to use [`event`][1] (due to its fragility), you could pass through `this` instead of `event`, which will refer to the button clicked like so:

&lt;!-- begin snippet: js hide: false console: true babel: false --&gt;

&lt;!-- language: lang-js --&gt;

